(38, 'Library', 'A library is an important asset for any center of higher learning which provides services and facilities to meet the requirements of learning, teaching, research & development and consultancy programs. Hence, efforts are always directed towards creating a very rich library having all important National and International journals/ newspapers, encyclopedia and magazines. The institution houses two libraries: Main library and Reference library. These libraries are a physical manifestation of our vision to distinguish the college as a center of resource in the knowledge era. The libraries aim to fulfill the crucial role of supporting learning and teaching activities to all members of the Institute.\r\n\r\nWith a collection of close to 40,000 books in addition to thousands of journals and theses, the library is one of the best in the region. It has been our endeavor to provide both students and faculty with the best possible research material including the latest writings of management gurus, popular management texts, classical books on management and much more.\r\n', 'Library'),
(44, 'about Us', '<h3 class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: ''open sans'', arial, sans-serif; font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.1; color: #333333; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 20px;">Welcome to IERT, Allahabad</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<blockquote class="custom-quote" style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 10px 20px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; font-size: 14px; border-left-width: 5px; border-left-style: solid; border-color: #a7c2d9; color: #333333; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;">\r\n<h3 style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: ''open sans'', arial, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.1; color: inherit; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 20px;">We serve the society by training professionals who can be leaders in innovation, entrepreneurship, creativity and management.</h3>\r\n<p class="people" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px 0px; color: #444444; font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5;"><span class="name" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #6091ba;">Vision</span><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" /><span class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px;">IERT, Allahabad</span></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;"><span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;">IERT is an engineering institute situated at the holy city of Allahabad.</span>&nbsp;The institute imparts Degree Engineering, Diploma Engineering &amp; Post Diploma in Computer Application and Management courses.&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;">IERT</span>&nbsp;has consistently produced great scholars and hence recognizing its potential the Government of UP awarded it Academic Autonomy for Diploma Engineering Courses.&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;">The Degree Division is affiliated to UP Technical University, Lucknow.</span><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" /><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />The campus of&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;">IERT</span>, Allahabad, India, spreads across 26.5 acres of vast land. The institute has well planned infrastructure, lush green gardens and well laid roads, along with equipped classrooms and state-of-the-art laboratories. The campus features an auditorium which has been the epic center of all the festivals and functions, held at the institution. It has been the hosting ground to every function, from the recreational Freshers'' parties to the emotional Farewell speeches. In addition to auditorium, there is a well-furnished air-conditioned seminar hall where important meetings and seminars take place. The institute has food courts providing quality food at subsidized rates.<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" /><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />Earlier,&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;">IERT</span>&nbsp;used to provide diploma courses only.&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;">In the year 2001, AICTE and State Govt. of U.P. upgraded this institute to Degree level to award Engineering degrees as well. Currently, the Institution is affiliated to UPTU, Lucknow.&nbsp;</span><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" /><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />The faculty at&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;">IERT</span>&nbsp;is well-qualified and one of the best among the other Engineering Institutes of the region. The Institute provides more than 50,000 books and journals including latest technical magazines. Workshops and seminars of various fields are held at regular intervals which enhances the practical as well as theoretical knowledge of the students.<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" /><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />Distinguished teachers from the most prestigious institutes of India, including MNNIT (Allahabad), JK Institute of Applied Physics (Allahabad) are invited as guest faculty.&nbsp;<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" /><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />Facilities available in&nbsp;<span style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;">IERT</span>&nbsp;includes:</p>\r\n<ul class="custom-list-style" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #333333; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">4 MBPS leased line with 24 hours of connectivity</li>\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">More than 200 computers with IBM PROLAN Server</li>\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">A separate CAD/CAM Lab for Industrial Production Branch</li>\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">Well-stocked libraries (Central Library &amp; Reference Library)</li>\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">Special emphasis on providing the students with practical knowledge</li>\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">Guest Faculty</li>\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">Industrial exposure through various Industrial Tours and Seminars</li>\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">Extra-curricular activities to promote all-round development</li>\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">Active participation in sporting events (in town or out of town)</li>\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">Hostel facilities</li>\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">Student Welfare Office for welfare of students</li>\r\n<li style="box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-bottom: 5px;">Classrooms with proper light, ventilation and furniture</li>\r\n</ul>', 'about'),
(45, 'History', '<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;"><img class="img-responsive" style="box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; display: block; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" src="http://iert.org.in/assets/images/750x300-about.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;">In 1955, Civil Engineering School was opened by a society named " Institute of Engineering &amp; Technology ". Late Shanker Saran, retired judge Hon''able High Court of Allahabad and Late Vishwamitra an advocate were respectively the President and Secretary of the society. This school was self sustaining it''s actvities. A good number of students were admitted every year. The students were awarded two years'' Diploma in Civil Engineering Course by the Board of Engineering College.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;">In 1962 U.P. Government took over this Institute by constituting a registered society named " Allahabad Engineering Polytechnic, Allahabad. "</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;">The society constituted a Board of Management/Managing Committee constituting of 11 members to manage affairs of the Polytechnic. The state government awarded the status of Grant in Aid to the Institute. The rules and by-laws of the society were accordingly framed and the Director of Technical Education, U.P. became ex-officio Secretary of Management Committee.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;">Reviewing the multifarious activities and the achievments of the Institute in the country and abroad, the U.P. Government changed the name of Allahabad Polytechnic to"Institute of Engineering and Rural Technology (I.E.R.T) " in 1982 and designated the post of "Director" in place of Principal, and the Institute was simultaneously awarded the Academic Autonomy. An Autonomy Committee was constituted and Secretary Technical Education, U.P. became ex-officio Chairman of the committee.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;">The Institute Of Engineering and Rural Technology Allahabad (IERT) was established in 1955.In the year 1962 it became the institution of the State under Grant in Aid. Subsequently in the year 1982 the Institute was awarded Academic Autonomy by the State Government. The governance of the institution remains under the predominant control of the State.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;">The institution had already established itself as a premier institution : rather the best among the very best in the country in diploma engineering programs. The institute maintains the same position.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;">The Engineering Degree Division of the Institute Of Engineering and Rural Technology, Allahabad was set up in 2001,when the college started offering degree courses in engineering with affiliation from U.P. Technical University , Lucknow (UP). It started it''s academic activities from October 2001 with the first batch joining the college on 30th October 2001. The Institute has a highly developed educational infrastructure and good faculty with an international outlook. The Institute aims to have a very active interaction with the industry and has a mission to serve society by training professionals who can be leaders in innovation, entrepreneurship, creativity and management.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;">The infrastructure of iert is rapidly increasing the no. of seats in each branch has increased and facilities provided to students are increasing day by day.</p>', 'history'),
(48, 'Contact us', '<article class="contact-form col-md-8 col-sm-7  page-row">\r\n<h3 class="title">Get in touch</h3>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;d love to hear from you. text</p>\r\n<form>\r\n<div class="form-group name"><label for="name">Name</label> <input id="name" class="form-control" type="text" placeholder="Enter your name" /></div>\r\n<!--//form-group-->\r\n<div class="form-group email"><label for="email">Email<span class="required">*</span></label> <input id="email" class="form-control" type="email" placeholder="Enter your email" /></div>\r\n<!--//form-group-->\r\n<div class="form-group phone"><label for="phone">Phone</label> <input id="phone" class="form-control" type="tel" placeholder="Enter your contact number" /></div>\r\n<!--//form-group-->\r\n<div class="form-group message"><label for="message">Message<span class="required">*</span></label> <textarea id="message" class="form-control" rows="6" placeholder="Enter your message here..."></textarea></div>\r\n<!--//form-group--> <button class="btn btn-theme" type="submit">Send message</button></form></article>\r\n<!--//contact-form-->', 'contact'),
(49, 'council', '<h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: ''open sans'', arial, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.1; color: #333333; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 24px;"><span class="style4" style="box-sizing: border-box;">Council Members:</span></h2>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;" align="justify">The institute has following Governing bodies:</p>\r\n<h3 style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: ''open sans'', arial, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.1; color: #333333; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 20px;">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<table style="box-sizing: border-box; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; max-width: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">\r\n<tbody style="box-sizing: border-box;">\r\n<tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">1</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Principal Secretary, Technical Education UP</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Chairman</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">2</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Director, IERT Allahabad</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Secretary</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">3</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Divisional Commissioner, Allahabad</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Member</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">4</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Director, Technical Education UP</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Member</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">5</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Director, MNNIT Allahabad</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Member</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">6</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Dean, Faculty of Science, Allahabad University</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Member</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">7</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Secretary Board of Technical Education, UP</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Member</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">8</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">NRO, AICTE</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Member</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">9</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Registrar, UP Technical University Lucknow</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Special Invitee</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">10</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">A Representative of State Govt. Finance Ministry</td>\r\n<td style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px;">Special Invitee<br /><br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'council'),
(50, 'Computer Science & engineering', '<h3 class="title">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<!--p><img class="img-responsive" src="assets/images/4.jpg" alt="" /></p-->\r\n<p>The Computer Science and Engineering Department was established in 2001 and is presently offering B.Tech degree course in Computer Science and Engineering. This course is affiliated to Gautam Buddha Technical University. To keep up with the integration of computer in every field of engineering and research, it features state of the art infrastructure. The total intake for Computer Science and Engineering branch is 60 to maintain a balanced structure of faculty-student ratio as per the AICTE norms.</p>\r\n<p>The theory lectures are supplemented with lab experiments, assignments and regular assessments. Separate labs are provided for the students of different semesters. These labs are related with work on Data Structure, Internet (Leased line), Data Network, Software Project, Multimedia, Computer Network, Web Technologies etc. The students are assigned various projects and assignments on interest basis. The languages referenced are: JAVA and Visual JAVA, C/C++/Visual C++,Visual Basic, HTML/XML/DHTML/Cgi-Bin/JAVA Script/CGI-Perl and other Web Technologies etc. The department is having various labs fully equipped with latest technology as listed below:</p>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-md-6">\r\n<h3 class="has-divider text-highlight">Labs</h3>\r\n<ul class="custom-list-style">\r\n<li>Client server &amp; Data Base</li>\r\n<li>Communication</li>\r\n<li>Compiler Construction</li>\r\n<li>Computer Graphics</li>\r\n<li>Computer Network</li>\r\n<li>Computer Organization</li>\r\n<li>Data Structures</li>\r\n<li>DBMS</li>\r\n<li>Information System</li>\r\n<li>Microprocessor</li>\r\n<li>MIS/li&gt;</li>\r\n<li>Multimedia,Electronics</li>\r\n<li>Numerical Techniques</li>\r\n<li>OOPS &amp; Algorithm</li>\r\n<li>Operating System</li>\r\n<li>Software Engineering</li>\r\n<li>UNIX &amp; C Programming</li>\r\n<li>Web Technology</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'cse'),
(51, 'Directer\\\\\\''s Message', '<article class=\\"course-item\\">\\r\\n<blockquote class=\\"custom-quote\\">\\r\\n<h3>We serve the society by training professionals who can be leaders in innovation, entrepreneurship, creativity and management.</h3>\\r\\n<p class=\\"people\\"><span class=\\"name\\">Vision</span><br /><span class=\\"title\\">IERT, Allahabad </span></p>\\r\\n</blockquote>\\r\\n<p class=\\"featured-image page-row\\"><img class=\\"img-responsive\\" src=\\"assets/images/courses/course-1.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" /></p>\\r\\n<div class=\\"page-row\\">\\r\\n<p>The world is fast changing. The world of technology even more so. Clearly the need of the hour is technocrats possessing leadership qualities with a global perspective on technological, economic &amp; cultural interfaces with business. A prerequisite of leadership is to look beyond the present. To be an innovator in technology or a stimulant of change in society, you need to extend your current knowledge and capabilities. Our objective is to prepare leaders, who go beyond conventional technical skills. I.E.R.T. is fast developing as a high quality institute of international standards in order to meet the needs of the fast changing 21st century world. The Institute not only provides high technology-based-education to students, but also lays emphasis on cultivation of modern outlook and promotion of rich and vibrant cultural heritage. It provides a congenial atmosphere for students to facilitate their development as balanced and mature human beings as they grow in life. The management aims to develop I.E.R.T. as a modern technical institute of our country. In a short span of time, it is already one of the top ranking colleges of the state.</p>\\r\\n</div>\\r\\n<!--//page-row--></article>\\r\\n<!--//course-item-->\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'dirdesks'),
(52, 'Electronics Engineering', '<div class=\\"row page-row\\">\\r\\n<p>The Department of Electronics Engineering was established in 2001 and it offers B. Tech in Electronics affiliated to UP Technical University. The Department takes an intake of 60 students each year. Electronics and communication is that field of engineering whose basic knowledge has become essential for all branches of engineering, because it is applicable to all in one form or other as ICs, Gates, MOSFETs, FETs, Transistors Diodes, Microprocessors etc. Keeping all in mind, the department offers the courses of basic electronics devices to all engineering branches in the first two years to enhance their abilities regarding the Electronic Devices and their various operations. Other major courses of Electronics and Communication engineering are also offered to engineering students of different branches depending upon their requirements. The main purpose of the department is not only to prepare the students to the real life opportunities as fabrication of circuit models for which they are made to do various mini and major projects, but also to prepare them in accordance with the developing technology. For this, effective method of teaching is adopted where the focus is given on practical application besides theory lectures.</p>\\r\\n</div>\\r\\n<div class=\\"row\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\"col-md-6\\">\\r\\n<h3 class=\\"has-divider text-highlight\\">Labs</h3>\\r\\n<ul class=\\"custom-list-style\\">\\r\\n<li>Analog Circuit</li>\\r\\n<li>Analog Communication</li>\\r\\n<li>Basic Electrical Engineering</li>\\r\\n<li>Communication</li>\\r\\n<li>Digital Communication</li>\\r\\n<li>Electronics Measurements &amp; Transducers</li>\\r\\n<li>Digital Circuit</li>\\r\\n<li>Digital Signal Processing</li>\\r\\n<li>Electrical Machine</li>\\r\\n<li>Electronics Device</li>\\r\\n<li>AElectronics Workshop &amp; PCB</li>\\r\\n<li>Integrated Circuits</li>\\r\\n<li>Electronics Workshop &amp; PCB</li>\\r\\n<li>Microprocessor</li>\\r\\n<li>MIS</li>\\r\\n<li>Multimedia, Electronics</li>\\r\\n<li>Network</li>\\r\\n<li>Power Electronics</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n</div>\\r\\n</div>', 'elex'),
(53, 'Facilities', '<article class=\\"course-item\\">\\r\\n<p class=\\"featured-image page-row\\"><img class=\\"img-responsive\\" src=\\"assets/images/courses/course-1.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" /></p>\\r\\n<div class=\\"page-row\\">\\r\\n<p align=\\"left\\"><strong>LIBRARY</strong></p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\">The College library is well equipped with an elaborate collection of books on various aspects of engineering and related subjects.</p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\">For more details <u> <a href=\\"library.php\\"><u>Click here</u></a></u></p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\"><strong>HOSTEL</strong></p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\">The college provides excellent hostel facilities for boys and girls. The hostels have 24 hours power supply with backup, telephone services, spacious dining halls where nutritious meals are served. The hostel campus has round-the-clock security.</p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\">For more details <u><a href=\\"hostel.php\\"><u>Click here</u></a></u></p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\"><strong>LABS</strong></p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\">The college labs have state-of-the-art equipment. The Computer Labs are provided with latest software and application development tools. The computer systems have UPS backup. The Electrical and Electronic Labs have latest equipment for application of engineering techniques.</p>\\r\\n<div align=\\"justify\\">&nbsp;</div>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\"><strong>TRAINING TOURS</strong></p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\">Industrial training tours are organized from time to time in leading industries to enable students to complement their theoretical knowledge with practical experience.</p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\"><strong>SEMINAR HALL</strong></p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\">A huge air conditioned conference hall with effective light and scientifically designed acoustics is excellent for hosting meetings, seminars and workshops. All presentation aids are available for the speakers and guests.</p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\"><strong>AUDITORIUM</strong></p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\">The institute has a huge auditorium with a seating capacity of 400-500 students. It has an effective light and sound system.</p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\"><strong>CANTEENS</strong></p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"left\\">The two canteens in college provide nutritious, hygienic and healthy food, at subsidized rates.</p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\"><strong>MEDICAL FACILITY</strong></p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\">The college provides adequate medical aid to all students at its medical center. A medical officer has been arranged to provide first aid and medical relief. The medical center is fully equipped with the latest medical facilities.</p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\"><strong>INSURANCE</strong></p>\\r\\n<p align=\\"justify\\">The students of I.E.R.T. are insured upto an amount of Rs. 2 Lakh.</p>\\r\\n</div>\\r\\n<!--//page-row--></article>\\r\\n<!--//course-item-->\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'facilities'),
(55, 'hostel', '<div class=\\"course-wrapper col-md-8 col-sm-7\\">\\r\\n<article class=\\"course-item\\">\\r\\n<p class=\\"featured-image page-row\\"><img class=\\"img-responsive\\" src=\\"assets/images/courses/course-1.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" /></p>\\r\\n<div class=\\"page-row\\">\\r\\n<p>Every effort has been made at the Institute of Engineering and Rural Technology to provide the best facilities for students who live on-campus. Every student has access to a wide range of activities, facilities and support. Besides the regular hostel dining facilities, there are affordable food services on campus that provide inexpensive and easily accessible meals.</p>\\r\\n<p>A Spacious Hostel is situated close to the Institution Campus at the bank of Ganges. I.E.R.T. with its beautifully landscaped and carefully tended gardens provides an ideal environment for a congenial learning experience. Here is a campus that invites students out of their hostels to spend time between classes midst greenery and a riot of floral colour. All rooms are provided with ceiling fans, bookracks &amp; wardrobes. Also each student residing in the hostel is given a bed, table and chair.</p>\\r\\n<p><strong>DIVISIONS:</strong> There are Ten Boy\\''s Hostel Blocks, which accommodate nearly 800 students in two bedded, three bedded, four bedded and six bedded rooms. The 3 girls\\'' hostels have capacity for 200 students. Optional washing services are provided. 24x7 Power facility with generator backup. The common room of the hostel is furnished with facilities of indoor games like Table Tennis, Carrom and Chess, television, magazines and newspapers. There is a small library for the inmates providing them necessary text-books. A small canteen and a general store is situated in the Hostel campus to meet the day-to-day needs of the hostel-residents. There is a gymnasium &amp; a dispensary in the hostel. There are wide open spaces in the hostel with well maintained respective courts of Badminton and Volleyball &amp; ground available for Cricket and Soccer. Newly admitted students in the Institute can get hostel admission. The selection is made on the basis of one\\''s merit, in the entrance test &amp; participation in extra &amp; co-curricular activities. The First Year students will have to apply to the Warden on the prescribed form for hostel admission at the time of admission. Seats are reserved for S.C./S.T. candidates as per the norms. Proper security measures are implemented for the welfare of the students.</p>\\r\\n<p><strong>DINING FACILITIES:</strong><br /> The spotlessly maintained and spacious vegetarian dining halls in the hostels serve wholesome food with the help of a unique steam cooking facility. Proper care is taken that food served to the hostellers is highly nutritious &amp; fresh. Breakfast, lunch, tea and dinner is served by the mess attendants.</p>\\r\\n<p>Fast food outlets are also attached to both the Boys and Girls Hostels.</p>\\r\\n</div>\\r\\n<!--//page-row--></article>\\r\\n<!--//course-item--></div>\\r\\n<!--//course-wrapper-->', 'hostel'),
(57, 'B.Tech', '<p>Admission to B.Tech. Ist semester, and B.Tech. IIIrd semester (for diploma holder candidates only) will be made as per the rules prescribed by the Academic Council of the U.P.Technical University.<br /><br />Admission To First Year<br /><br />Admission to 1st semester B.Tech is through State Entrance Examination conducted by UP Technical University, Lucknow Uttar Pradesh.<br /><br />In all state / state funded engineering and technological institutions and in all private engineering colleges, 5% seats are available for Non Resident Indians . Admission to all other seats shall be made as per latest orders issued by U.P. Govt. The Tuition and other fee shall be decided by the State Government.<br /><br />Direct Admission To Second Year<br /><br />Candidates who have passed 3/4 year Diploma (with minimum 60% marks) recognized by the U.P. Board of Technical Education in any branch of Engineering / Technology except Agriculture Engg. are eligible for admission to Second year in any branch of Engg./ Technology except Agriculture Engg.&nbsp;<br /><br />NRI Quota<br /><br />NRI candidates, who possess minimum requisite qualification, may get direct admission on 5% seats of total intake. Such candidates should submit the application forms but need not appear in the Admission Test. Seat allotment for filling NRI quota will be made before the start of counseling of UPTU qualified candidates. The candidates will be informed separately about the date of allotment of seat under this quota, and they are required to be present on the day of counseling.</p>', 'btech'),
(59, 'Addmission in Diploma', '<p><span style=\\"color: #333333; font-family: \\''Helvetica Neue\\'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;\\">Refer to the brochure obtained with admission form.</span></p>', 'diploma'),
(60, 'Insdustrial Production', '<p class=\\"featured-image page-row\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 30px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: \\''Helvetica Neue\\'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;\\"><img class=\\"img-responsive\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; display: block; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\\" src=\\"http://iert.org.in/assets/images/courses/ip.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" /></p>\\r\\n<div class=\\"page-row\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 30px; color: #333333; font-family: \\''Helvetica Neue\\'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444;\\">&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n<span style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\\">The Department of Industrial &amp; Production Engineering</span>&nbsp;offers B.Tech program in affiliation to UP Technical University. Since its foundation in 2001 the department strives to graduate industrial and production engineers of highest quality and to conduct state of the art research. The department ensures the availability of high quality and relevent engineering education to all aspirants as per the curriculum of the university. The department dedicate&Acirc; itself to providing students with a set of skills, knowledge and attitudes that will permit its graduates to succeed and thrive as engineers. The programme prepares its graduates to pursue life-long learning, serve the profession and meet intellectual, ethical and career challenges. It also maintain a vital, state-of-the art research environment to provide its students and faculty with opportunities to create, interpret, apply and disseminate knowledge.<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" /><br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />Industrial &amp; Production Engineering covers areas such as Fluid Mechanics, Thermal Sciences, Material Sciences, IC Engines, Mechanical Systems, Human Factors, Concurrent Engineering and Intelligent Systems etc. This department has a strong backup from the pre-existent labs and workshops of the institute. The institute has unmatched workshop facilities. The graphics faculty is also very seasoned. The department emphasizes focused educational&Acirc; and research programs of exceptional high quality. The department faculty also collaborate with researchers at different University.&nbsp;</div>', 'ip'),
(61, 'Electrical Engineering', '<p class=\\"featured-image page-row\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 30px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: \\''Helvetica Neue\\'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;\\"><img class=\\"img-responsive\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; display: block; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\\" src=\\"http://iert.org.in/assets/images/courses/ee.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" /></p>\\r\\n<div class=\\"page-row\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 30px; color: #333333; font-family: \\''Helvetica Neue\\'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444;\\">Electrical Engineering&nbsp;is a field of&nbsp;engineering&nbsp;that generally deals with the study and application of&nbsp;electricity,&nbsp;electronics, and&nbsp;electromagnetism. It now covers a wide range of subfields including&nbsp;Electronics,&nbsp;Digital Computers,&nbsp;Power Engineering, Telecommunications, Control Systems, RF Engineering and Signal Processing.<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" /><br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />Fundamental to the discipline are the sciences of Physics and Mathematics, as these help to obtain both a qualitative and quantitative description of how such systems will work. Today most of the engineering techniques involve the use of computers, and it is commonplace to use computer-aided design programs when designing electrical systems. Nevertheless, the ability to sketch ideas is still invaluable for quickly communicating with others; hence, the institute provides the best and hardworking faculty for the understanding of the practical concepts of this branch giving the best outcome through the students.</p>\\r\\n<p style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444;\\" align=\\"justify\\">The department has rich and experience faculty members. The continuous updating in the&nbsp; course curriculum polishes the budding electrical engineers, in a way, so as to meet the challenges posed by the latest technologies and reach the ever-expanding horizons. The experience, expertise and enriched knowledge of the faculty members are the distinguishing features of this department.&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n<p style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444;\\">Along with the theory lectures, implying the studies of DC and AC machines, EMI, Analog and Digital, EMFT, Elements of Power System, Power Electronics, Microprocessor, Power System Analysis, Instrumentation &amp; Process Control, etc. The Institute also provides the practical application of these subjects through various labs fully equipped with latest technology and instruments. The Lab work includes the Network Lab, EMMI lab, Control lab, NT lab, Process Control lab, Electronics lab, Electrical Simulation Lab, Power Electronics Lab and Communication Engineering lab.</p>\\r\\n<p style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444;\\" align=\\"justify\\">&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n</div>', 'ee'),
(62, 'Instrumentation & control Engineering', '<p class=\\"featured-image page-row\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 30px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: \\''Helvetica Neue\\'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;\\"><img class=\\"img-responsive\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; display: block; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\\" src=\\"http://iert.org.in/assets/images/courses/ic.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" /></p>\\r\\n<div class=\\"page-row\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 30px; color: #333333; font-family: \\''Helvetica Neue\\'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444;\\" align=\\"justify\\"><span style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\\">Instrumentation</span>&nbsp;is defined as the art and science of measurement and control of process variables within a production or manufacturing area.<span style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\\">&nbsp;</span><br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />An instrument is a device that measures a physical quantity such as flow, temperature, level, distance, angle, or pressure. Instruments may be as simple as direct reading thermometer or may be complex such as multi-variable process analyzers. Instruments are often part of a control system in refineries, factories, and vehicles. The control of processes is one of the main branches of applied instrumentation. Instrumentation can also refer to handheld devices that measure some desired variable. Diverse handheld instrumentation is common in laboratories, but can be found in the household as well. For example, a smoke detector is a common instrument found in most western homes.<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />Instruments attached to a control system may provide signals used to operate solenoids, valves, regulators, circuit breakers, or relays. These devices control a desired output variable, and provide either remote or automated control capabilities. These are often referred to as final control elements when controlled remotely or by a control system.<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />The Department of Instrumentation and Control Systems Engineering was established in the year 1975(diploma division) and was extended to degree division in the year 2010.<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />The Department provides undergraduate program (B.Tech)<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />in Instrumentation and Control Engineering Instrumentation and control engineering play<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />a vital role in any modern industry. We aim at producing talented instrumentation and control specialists who cater to the needs of the modern industries. The department is a fascinating motley of multifarious disciplines of technology such as Electronics, Electrical, and Mechanical Measurements, Process Control Engineering. The curriculum begins with foundation courses in mathematics, physics, chemistry, electronics and mechanics. Emphasis is on the courses like Sensors and Transducers, Micro-controllers, Industrial Instrumentation, Control Systems, PC interfacing and Telemetry.</p>\\r\\n<p style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444;\\" align=\\"justify\\"><span style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\\">Proctor</span>- Mr. Sunil Kr Dubey<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" /><span style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\\">H.O.D</span>.- &nbsp;Mr.S.P.Gautam<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" /><span style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\\">Faculty</span>- Mr.S.M. Kar<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Animesh Konch<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.S.V.Srivastava<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Anurag Yadav</p>\\r\\n</div>', 'ic'),
(63, 'Mechanical Engineering', '<p class=\\"featured-image page-row\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 30px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: \\''Helvetica Neue\\'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;\\"><img class=\\"img-responsive\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; display: block; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\\" src=\\"http://iert.org.in/assets/images/courses/mech.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" /></p>\\r\\n<div class=\\"page-row\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 30px; color: #333333; font-family: \\''Helvetica Neue\\'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;\\">&lt;\\r\\n<p style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444;\\" align=\\"justify\\"><span style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\\">Mechanical engineering</span>&nbsp;is a discipline of&nbsp;engineering&nbsp;that applies the principles of engineering,&nbsp;physics&nbsp;and&nbsp;materials science&nbsp;for analysis, design, manufacturing, and maintenance of&nbsp;mechanical&nbsp;systems. It is the branch of engineering that involves the production and usage of&nbsp;heat&nbsp;and mechanical power for the design, production, and operation of&nbsp;machines&nbsp;and&nbsp;tools.&nbsp;It is one of the oldest and broadest&nbsp;engineering disciplines.</p>\\r\\n<p style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444;\\" align=\\"justify\\">The department of Mechanical Engineering was established in 2010 .It is one of the premier departments of the Institute .The department offers an undergraduate four year degree course. The curriculum of these programs encompasses latest developments in the field as well as present day and future needs of Industries.<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" /><br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mechanical Engineers rolling out from the institute are well groomed specially in the areas of software development/handling and Research and Development activities apart from traditional areas. Continuous updation in the current syllabus improves the mindset and advances the budding engineers to meet the challenge posed by the updated technologies in the future . Department has enriched potential and dedicated faculty members whose whole hearted involvement is the biggest strength.</p>\\r\\n</div>', 'me'),
(64, 'Civil Engineering', '<p class=\\"featured-image page-row\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 30px; color: #444444; font-size: 15px; font-family: \\''Helvetica Neue\\'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 21.4286px;\\"><img class=\\"img-responsive\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; display: block; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\\" src=\\"http://iert.org.in/assets/images/courses/civil.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" /></p>\\r\\n<div class=\\"page-row\\" style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 30px; color: #333333; font-family: \\''Helvetica Neue\\'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #444444;\\" align=\\"justify\\"><span style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\\">Civil engineering</span>&nbsp;is a professional engineering discipline that deals with the design, construction, and maintenance of the physical and artificially built environment. It including works like roads, bridges, canals, dams, and buildings. Civil engineering is one of the oldest and most reputed engineering streams. It is traditionally broken into several sub-disciplines including environmental engineering, geotechnical engineering, geophysics, geodesy, control engineering, structural engineering, transportation engineering, earth science, atmospheric sciences, forensic engineering, municipal or urban engineering, water resource engineering, materials engineering, offshore engineering, quantity surveying, coastal engineering, surveying, and construction engineering. Civil engineering takes place on all levels: in the public sector from municipal&nbsp; to national governments, and in the private sector from individual homeowners to international companies.<br style=\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\" />The department was established in the year 1955, with the institute itself. Later on in the year 2011,it was extended from diploma to degree (B.Tech).</p>\\r\\n</div>', 'civil');
